  "body": "Looking at running a full archive node of Geth using the new PBS, coming from 1.12.2 going to 1.13.2 and while I read the blog post for 1.13.0 the `--history` flags appear to be undocumented.\r\n\r\nTypically to run a full archive node we need `--gcmode=archive` and `--syncmode=full`\r\n\r\nIn addition to that we'd usually want `--txlookuplimit=0` - seeing the latest release this is now aliased to `--history.transactions` which is fine.\r\n\r\nHowever, `history.state` seems undocumented and I do not know just based on the description if I need to set this, or how it impacts the node.\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n    --history.state value               (default: 90000)                   ($GETH_HISTORY_STATE)\r\n          Number of recent blocks to retain state history for (default = 90,000 blocks, 0\r\n          = entire chain)\r\n```\r\n\r\nMy gut tells me I want to set this to `0` for a full archive node but exactly what this does, especially in relation to `gcmode=archive`",
